Monique Duval Hanover Park residents host a peaceful picket. (SAPS) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Hanover Park residents took to the streets on Tuesday (25 April) to express their unhappiness after women were hit by stray bullets following a shooting between rival gangs.&nbsp;Philippi police spokesperson, Captain Lance Goliath, says the aim of the peaceful picket was to make residents aware of the crime situation and to make a plea to police and local government to step up their involvement in fighting crime. &ldquo;Police kept a watchful eye and after picketing the participants dispersed peacefully. No negative incidents were reported. Police will maintain a zero tolerance approach in combating crime,&rdquo; says Goliath.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.